About Nubank
Nubank is the leading fintech in Latin America. Using bleeding-edge technology, design and data, the company aims to fight complexity and empower people to take control of their finances. We are disrupting an outdated and bureaucratic system by building a simple, safe and 100% digital environment that addresses customers’ needs with no paperwork, bank branches or inefficient call centers.
Our headquarters is located in São Paulo, Brazil, we have new offices in Buenos Aires and we are also present in Mexico City as well as in Berlin, Germany with an engineering office. With a team of over 1,500 of the most innovative professionals in technology, Nubank is dedicated to creating an inclusive, international and challenging work environment.
About the role

The Internal Audit IT Specialists are part of the Internal Audit IT Pack, and are the reference in Information Technology and Security subjects for other auditors and other teams, playing a key role in keeping IA up-to-date on what is happening in Nubank’s technology environment, conducting, executing and acting as a consultant in audit fieldworks, bringing inputs to the annual work plan and enhancing the IT auditors’ knowledge and skills.

You will be responsible for


Gathering data and analyzing risks to build the annual audit work plan;
Participating in and conducting audit fieldworks, executing tests and producing the final report along with the team;
Acting as a consultant on the subject of your expertise, assisting and guiding other auditors;
Interacting with stakeholders from the first and second lines of defense, discussing and following up on findings and action plans implementation;
Acting as a knowledge multiplier, sharing your experience and training other auditors to enhance the team's IT skills;
Acting as a technical leader for more junior auditors;
Actively participating in Internal Audit's strategic projects.


We are looking for a person who has


Solid experience in auditing the IT environment, preferably in financial institutions;
Solid knowledge and experience in applying commonly used IT frameworks and standards in the audit program;
Knowledge of cloud-based environments (preferably AWS);
Knowledge of SQL, Scala or other data manipulation language;
Knowledge of programming languages;
Intermediate English level;
Knowledge in financial market regulation related to technology (e.g. CMN Resolution 4,893 from Bacen);
Incessant curiosity and desire to continuously study and understand the surroundings as Nubank constantly evolves and changes;
Disposal to share knowledge, guide other professionals and follow-up on their technical development;
Desire to create new and more efficient ways of assessing the company's risks;
Ability to constantly adapt and deal with new technologies and tools.
